# refactor-extraction-plan-unverified-assumptions - History

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-26)

**Changed by:** Session context (ProjectHephaestus issue #1408 implementation-plan risk capture)
**Verification:** unverified

### What changed
- Added boundary-safe shared utility extraction risks for plans that move subprocess/Git helper bodies into a lower-level utility module.
- Added reviewer focus for stale line-number/search evidence, assumed helper names and exports, hidden dependency/import-cycle risk, behavioral parity, and over-broad retry wrappers.
- Updated the reusable checklist with exact source-assumption categories an implementer must re-verify before coding.

### Why
The captured implementation plan had not been executed end-to-end and relied on remembered or previously generated search output. Reviewers need a durable checklist that separates plan intent from unverified source assumptions before approving a shared utility refactor.

